Learn how = . [image: Search] Find what you need fast With the power of Google Search right in your inbox, it's easy to sort your email. Find what you're looking for with predictions based on email content, past searches and contacts. [image: Search] Much more than email You can send text messages and make video calls with Hangouts right from Gmail. To use this feature on mobile, download the Hangouts app for Android and Apple devices. subject: Stay more organized with Gmail's inbox
text:
--001a11487338b57ed8053448bfd2 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable Stay more organized with Gmail's inbox [image: Google] Hi Byod Gmail's inbox puts you in control [image: Inbox video] Meet the inbox Gmail's inbox sorts your email into categories so you can see what's new at a glance, decide which emails you want to read when and view similar types of emails together. Watch the video [image: Social tab] Choose your categories The Social and Promotions categories are on by default. Add categories like Updates and Forums or remove categories to have those emails show up in your Primary inbox. Learn how to choose categories [image: Customize] Customize your inbox If you see a message you want in a different category, you can move it there. On mobile devices, you can even choose which categories create a notification. More customization tips To learn more about Gmail's inbox, check out the help center or watch= the video . [image: Gmail icon] Happy emailing, The Gmail Team =C2=A9 2016 Google Inc. 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043 --001a11487338b57ed8053448bfd2 Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable Stay more organized with Gmail's inbox

subject: Fwd: In or Out: TTIP
text:
--001a11468de6e0efd1053563fa2b Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable ---------- Forwarded message ---------- From: Trish Murray - 38 Degrees Date: Wed, Jun 15, 2016 at 6:51 PM Subject: In or Out: TTIP To: Alexandru Mereacre [image: 38 Degrees Logo] Dear Alexandru, *What=E2=80=99s the deal with TTIP and the EU Referendum? Truth is, it=E2= =80=99s complicated. *A team of independent fact-checkers has looked at every possible scenario - and *they simply can=E2=80=99t say for certain what vot= ing =E2=80=98In=E2=80=99 or =E2=80=98Out=E2=80=99 will mean for TTIP.* [1] It=E2=80=99s not a headli= ne-grabbing answer, but it=E2=80=99s the right one. Together, we can make sure that as many people as possible have the facts before they vote.* Please can you help share the facts about TTIP and the EU with everyone you know?* Just click the image below to watch the 60 second video, then share it with your friends and family: SHARE THE FACTS *Here=E2=80=99s a detailed breakdown of what we do know:* - If TTIP passes, and we stay in the EU, the UK will be subject to TTIP - The UK Parliament can block TTIP if it wanted - and other EU countries can kill the deal too - But if we stay in the EU, and TTIP passes, the agreement and any changes in EU legislation that result from it will apply to the UK. - If we left the EU, we will not be subject to TTIP. But the government may try to make a trade deal with the US covering similar ground. - Leaving the EU doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily mean the UK would be unaffe= cted by TTIP. This depends on the type of deal the UK negotiates. If we left the single market TTIP would have minimal impact. If we joined the European Economic Area and stayed in the single market, any change in EU regulati= ons because of TTIP would affect the UK. - If we leave, the UK may decide to negotiate its own deal with America because it=E2=80=99s an important market. But both the US President and = his Trade Representative have cast doubt on whether a deal with the UK would be an immediate priority in the short term. This will depend on the US administration at the time we left the EU. - Right now it=E2=80=99s impossible to be certain about the end result o= f TTIP, as the text still hasn=E2=80=99t been released. The negotiators want to = agree TTIP in before a new president takes office in the USA, but no fixed date has been set. *It can feel frustrating not to have a definite answer *one way or the other. *But there=E2=80=99s one thing worse than frustration - and that=E2= =80=99s political point-scoring ruining any chance of a proper, grown-up debate on such an important decision.* 38 Degrees members decided together to cut through the spin on the EU Referendum. [2] *If each of us shares the reality about TTIP and the EU with everyone we know, we can make sure as many people as possible head to the polling station armed with the facts.* Can you share the video on TTIP and the EU Referendum now? SHARE THE FACTS Thanks for being involved, Trish, Bex, Laura and the 38 Degrees team PS: If you want to chat with other 38 Degrees members about the EU Referendum and TTIP, you can join a discussion on Facebook now by clicking the link below: https://secure.38degrees.org.uk/TTIP-EU-fact-video-fbpost NOTES: [1] The fact check has been made using research by Full Fact. Full Fact is an independent, fact checking charity. They=E2=80=99re an organisation who = use experts, research and investigations to check claims made by politicians and the media. You can find out more about Full Fact and the work they do on their website here: https://fullfact.org/about/ [2] Here=E2=80=99s how 38 Degrees members voted on what to do together in t= he EU Referendum: https://home.38degrees.org.uk/2016/03/07/the-eu-referendum-survey-results/ ------------------------------ 38 Degrees is funded by donations from thousands of members across the UK. Making a regular donation will mean 38 Degrees can stay independent and plan for future campaigns. Please will you chip in a few pounds a week? Start a direct debit ------------------------------ [image: Work with 38 Degrees] ------------------------------ Unsubscribe: If you no longer wish to be part of our movement and receive our emails you can unsubscribe here . This email was sent to mereacre@gmail.com.p> *38 DEGREES* Limited by guarantee Registered Company No. 6642193 in England and Wales Registered office: 40 Bowling Green Lane, London, EC1R 0NE --001a11468de6e0efd1053563fa2b Content-Type: text/html; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

From: Trish Murray - 38 Degre= es <act= ion@38degrees.org.uk>

To: Alexandru Mereacre <mereacre@gmail.com>

Dear Alexandru,

What=E2=80=99s the deal with TTIP and the E= U Referendum? Truth is, it=E2=80=99s complicated. A team of indepe= ndent fact-checkers has looked at every possible scenario - and the= y simply can=E2=80=99t say for certain what voting =E2=80=98In=E2=80=99 or = =E2=80=98Out=E2=80=99 will mean for TTIP. [1] It=E2=80=99s not a h= eadline-grabbing answer, but it=E2=80=99s the right one.

Together, we can make sure that as many people as possible have the facts = before they vote. Please can you help share the facts about TTIP an= d the EU with everyone you know? Just click the image below to wat= ch the 60 second video, then share it with your friends and family:
=C2=A0


SHARE THE FACTS

Here=E2=80=99s a detailed breakdown of what we do know:

  • If TTIP passes, and we stay in the EU, the UK will be subject to TTI= P
  • The UK Parliament can block TTIP if it wanted - and other EU countri= es can kill the deal too
  • But if we stay in the EU, and TTIP passes, the agreement and any cha= nges in EU legislation that result from it will apply to the UK.
  • If we left the EU, we will not be subject to TTIP. But the governmen= t may try to make a trade deal with the US covering similar ground.
  • Leaving the EU doesn=E2=80=99t necessarily mean the UK would be unaf= fected by TTIP. This depends on the type of deal the UK negotiates. If we l= eft the single market TTIP would have minimal impact. If we joined the Euro= pean Economic Area and stayed in the single market, any change in EU regula= tions because of TTIP would affect the UK.
  • If we leave, the UK may decide to negotiate its own deal with Americ= a because it=E2=80=99s an important market. But both the US President and h= is Trade Representative have cast doubt on whether a deal with the UK would= be an immediate priority in the short term. This will depend on the US adm= inistration at the time we left the EU.
  • Right now it=E2=80=99s impossible to be certain about the end result= of TTIP, as the text still hasn=E2=80=99t been released. The negotiators w= ant to agree TTIP in before a new president takes office in the USA, but no= fixed date has been set.

It can feel frustrating not to have a definite answer one= way or the other. But there=E2=80=99s one thing worse than frustra= tion - and that=E2=80=99s political point-scoring ruining any chance of a p= roper, grown-up debate on such an important decision.

38 Degrees members decided together to cut through the spin on the EU Refe= rendum. [2] If each of us shares the reality about TTIP and the EU = with everyone we know, we can make sure as many people as possible head to = the polling station armed with the facts.

Can you share the video on TTIP and the EU Referendum now?

SHARE THE FACTS

Thanks for being involved,

Trish, Bex, Laura and the 38 Degrees team

https://secure.38deg= rees.org.uk/TTIP-EU-fact-video-fbpost

NOTES:
[1] The fact check has been made using research by Full Fact. Full Fact is= an independent, fact checking charity. They=E2=80=99re an organisation who= use experts, research and investigations to check claims made by politicia= ns and the media. You can find out more about Full Fact and the work they d= o on their website here:
https://fullfact.org/about/
